 &quot;The Romans will be expecting our attack.&quot; She said plainly as she looked at her broken sword. She then looked down at her wounds, seeing that they were bleeding thru the bandages again. She decided then, that searing the wounds was the only way to stop the excess blood loss.<br>
 &quot;We need to take a count of weapons, and we need to have eyes on the village, perferably animal.&quot; Solari said, casting a glance to Elektra, knowing how she felt. &quot;Then we will make plans to attack the Romans. If we were to go in there right now, they will surely kill Hipployte. But if we wait, in two days time the moon is no longer in the sky, they will hear the call of the amazons.&quot; <br>
