&quot;Would you care to ride, Marpe?&quot; She asked softly. Solari felt something hit her inside like a slap in the face when she looked at the warrior. Something that she had not felt in a long time. This was not the time, nor the place for those feelings to hit her and she quickly got them under control. Hoping that her eyes did not give her away. <br>
  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daughterofshylock>Daughter of Shylock</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 252<br> <font color=#993300>(3/27/03 11:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=133>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Battle changes</span><hr size=1> Alysia listened and then she turned her head towards Solari as they all began to walk towards the camp. Alysia wasnt a rational person. She was willing to go into the Roman camp and let loose on whatever crossed her path. But Solari was right.<br>
<br>
Alysia looked into the hills that surrounded them and whistled lightly. Yellow eyes appeared all over the darkened area. She smiled and then whispered.<br>
<br>
&quot;Go, find her, and keep watch.&quot;<br>
<br>
Each of the hidden wolves ran off into the woods and did as commanded. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">~*~ Jessica ~*~<br>
