<br>
&quot;Efharisto, Vasilissa Solari,&quot;  Marpe smiled as she took Solari's hand and pulled herself up on the back of the horse. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=solariwolf@amazonsunite>solariwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Themiscryian War Queen</span><br>  Posts: 161<br> <font color=#993300>(3/29/03 5:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=135>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Battle changes</span><hr size=1> Solari smiled as Marpe climbed up, hiding the pain that once again was rumbling thru her body. She urged her mare forward, following those who had already left for the encampment. <br>
 Solari kept a eye out for any surprises that the Romans might have, seeing as they might have decided to return. She kept her mind busy with a possible plan of attack and rescue. This was where she was skilled at..but this was going to require extra care...her queen, her own blood was the one being rescued this time and the plan had to be perfect so no harm would come to Hipployte or her fellow amazons. <br>
 &quot;Marpe.&quot; Solari said quietly. &quot;What's going on between you and Elektra?&quot;  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=solariwolf@amazonsunite>solariwolf</A> at: 3/30/03 1:02:41 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=marpeamzn>Marpe Amzn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 76<br> <font color=#993300>(4/2/03 12:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=136>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/MarpeAmznrpg.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Battle changes</span><hr size=1> The guard was surprised by the question, glancing around and then forward to their path.  &quot;There is nothing truly between Elektra and I.  For that most part, as a guard, I have always been trained to be wary of assassins.  And second, I know Elektra.  She has always been irrational.   She does things without thinking about it first.  Elektra is only upset with me now, because I told her to not take off and rescue Hippolyte on her own.  I could read her.  And she hates that...that and taking orders from me.&quot;<br>
